<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Business &amp; Sports Travel Safety for Corporate Teams -- SafeTrekr</title>
  <meta name="description" content="SafeTrekr assigns a professional safety analyst to review every business trip, team retreat, and tournament your organization sends -- across 17 dimensions of risk. Government intelligence. Duty of care documentation. Enterprise safety at per-trip pricing.">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Travel Safety Built for Corporate &amp; Sports Organizations">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Professional analyst review, government intelligence, and duty of care documentation for every business trip and tournament. Enterprise safety at per-trip pricing.">
  <meta property="og:image" content="/og/solutions-corporate.png">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://safetrekr.com/solutions/corporate">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="design-tokens.css">
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
  <script>
    tailwind.config = {
      theme: {
        extend: {
          colors: {
            background: '#e7ecee',
            foreground: '#061a23',
            card: '#f7f8f8',
            border: '#b8c3c7',
            ring: '#365462',
            muted: { DEFAULT: '#e7ecee', foreground: '#4d5153' },
            primary: {
              50: '#f1f9f4', 100: '#e0f1e6', 200: '#c0e2cd', 300: '#96cfac',
              400: '#6cbc8b', 500: '#4ca46e', 600: '#3f885b', 700: '#33704b',
              800: '#2a5b3d', 900: '#20462f', 950: '#132a1c',
              DEFAULT: '#3f885b', foreground: '#ffffff'
            },
            secondary: {
              DEFAULT: '#123646', foreground: '#f7f8f8',
              light: '#1a4a5e', muted: '#b8c3c7'
            },
            destructive: { DEFAULT: '#c1253e', foreground: '#ffffff' },
            safety: { green: '#22c55e', yellow: '#eab308', red: '#ef4444' },
            dark: {
              surface: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.1)',
              'text-primary': '#f7f8f8',
              'text-secondary': '#b8c3c7',
              accent: '#6cbc8b'
            }
          },
          fontFamily: {
            heading: ['Plus Jakarta Sans', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            body: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            mono: ['JetBrains Mono', 'ui-monospace', 'monospace']
          },
          maxWidth: {
            'container': '1280px'
          }
        }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: BreadcrumbList -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Solutions", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Corporate & Sports Teams", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions/corporate" }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: FAQPage -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is SafeTrekr just for international trips?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Any trip that takes your employees or athletes away from their normal work or training environment benefits from professional safety review. Domestic business travel to unfamiliar cities, regional conferences, client site visits, and domestic tournaments all carry risks that your organization has a duty to assess. Our domestic trip review costs $450. International review costs $1,250. The same 17-section analysis applies regardless of destination." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does SafeTrekr help with duty of care compliance?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Duty of care requires organizations to take reasonable steps to protect the health and safety of employees during work-related activities -- including travel. SafeTrekr produces the documented evidence that your organization conducted a professional safety assessment before each trip." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can sports organizations use SafeTrekr for tournament travel?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. SafeTrekr is specifically designed to handle tournament travel for youth and adult sports organizations. Our analyst reviews tournament venues, hotel safety, ground transportation, emergency medical facilities, and local conditions." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What about SafeSport compliance for youth sports?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The SafeSport Act requires youth-serving sports organizations to implement safety policies and report abuse. SafeTrekr's safety binder documents the safety protocols your organization established for each tournament or travel event." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How quickly do we get the safety binder back?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "3-5 business days from trip submission to binder delivery. For organizations that plan travel well in advance, this timeline fits naturally into your booking process." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do we need to sign an annual contract?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. SafeTrekr operates on a per-trip basis. No annual contract. No minimum trip count. No multi-month enterprise onboarding. Submit a trip, receive a safety binder, pay per trip." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can our travel coordinator submit trips on behalf of team leaders?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Trip submission is a guided 10-step wizard that takes 15-20 minutes. Your travel coordinator, HR team, or any designated administrator can submit trips on behalf of team leaders." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does pricing work for organizations with many trips?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each trip is priced independently -- $450 for domestic, $750 for extended domestic (multi-day), $1,250 for international. Organizations booking 15 or more trips per year qualify for volume pricing." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What does the mobile app provide during the trip?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Every trip leader gets the SafeTrekr mobile app with live geofencing, muster check-ins, rally point navigation, SMS broadcast capability, and morning/evening safety briefings." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can SafeTrekr handle international business travel to high-risk regions?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Many business trips involve destinations with elevated risk profiles -- emerging markets, regions with political instability, or locations with limited medical infrastructure." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does SafeTrekr compare to travel risk management platforms?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Enterprise travel risk management platforms like International SOS, WorldAware, or Crisis24 serve large corporations with dedicated security teams and six-figure annual budgets. SafeTrekr provides the core safety documentation these platforms generate at a per-trip price point accessible to mid-market organizations." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can legal counsel and risk management access the safety binder directly?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. You control access to each trip's safety binder. It can be shared with legal counsel, risk management, HR, insurance carriers, or any other stakeholder who needs to review safety preparation." }}
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    /* Dot grid background pattern */
    .bg-dot-grid {
      background-image: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-border) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 24px 24px;
    }

    /* Sticky in-page nav */
    .page-nav {
      position: sticky;
      top: 72px;
      z-index: 20;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      transform: translateY(-100%);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, opacity 0.3s ease;
    }
    .page-nav.visible {
      transform: translateY(0);
      opacity: 1;
    }
    .page-nav-inner {
      overflow-x: auto;
      -ms-overflow-style: none;
      scrollbar-width: none;
      scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    }
    .page-nav-inner::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
    .page-nav-link {
      scroll-snap-align: start;
      white-space: nowrap;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
      border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .page-nav-link:hover { color: var(--color-foreground); }
    .page-nav-link.active {
      color: var(--color-primary-700);
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary-500);
    }

    /* Accordion */
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .faq-trigger {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      width: 100%;
      padding: 20px 0;
      background: none;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      text-align: left;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.25rem);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--color-foreground);
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .faq-trigger:hover { color: var(--color-primary-700); }
    .faq-trigger svg {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }
    .faq-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }
    .faq-content {
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
    }
    .faq-content.open {
      max-height: 800px;
    }
    .faq-content-inner {
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 0.875rem + 0.15vw, 1rem);
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
    }

    /* Hero visual composition */
    .hero-visual {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 520px;
    }
    .hero-map {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 4/3;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d4dce0 0%, #c8d3d8 40%, #bcc8ce 100%);
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }
    .hero-map svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
    .hero-binder-card {
      position: absolute;
      top: -16px;
      right: -16px;
      width: 260px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .hero-status-badge {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 24px;
      left: 16px;
    }

    /* Binder preview stack */
    .binder-stack { position: relative; width: 100%; max-width: 360px; padding: 20px; }
    .binder-page {
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 24px;
      position: absolute;
      width: 100%;
    }
    .binder-page-back {
      transform: rotate(-2deg) translate(-12px, -16px);
      opacity: 0.7;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }
    .binder-page-mid {
      transform: rotate(-1deg) translate(-6px, -8px);
      opacity: 0.9;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    }
    .binder-page-front {
      position: relative;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
    }

    /* Comparison table layout */
    .comparison-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .comparison-row {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 0;
      }
      .comparison-item + .comparison-item {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-top: 16px;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }
    }

    /* Feature card link arrow hover */
    .feature-card:hover .arrow-icon {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .arrow-icon {
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    /* Site header */
    .site-header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 30;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.95);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    /* Smooth scroll */
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      html { scroll-behavior: auto; }
    }

    /* Animation keyframe */
    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
    .animate-fade-up {
      animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease forwards;
    }

    /* Mobile menu */
    .mobile-menu { display: none; }
    .mobile-menu.open { display: flex; }

    /* Pricing card highlight */
    .pricing-card-highlight {
      position: relative;
      border-color: var(--color-primary-400);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md), 0 0 0 1px var(--color-primary-200);
    }
  </style>
  <script src="https://mcp.figma.com/mcp/html-to-design/capture.js" async></script>
</head>
<body class="font-body" style="background: var(--color-background); color: var(--color-foreground);">

  <!-- Skip navigation -->
  <a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:bg-white focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded-md focus:shadow-lg focus:text-primary-700 focus:font-semibold focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring">
    Skip to main content
  </a>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       SITE HEADER
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <header id="site-header" class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-30 transition-all duration-300" style="height: 80px;">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 h-full flex items-center justify-between">
      <!-- Logo: Horizontal lockup -->
      <a href="/" aria-label="SafeTrekr home" class="flex-shrink-0">
        <svg height="32" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hidden lg:block" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
        <svg height="28" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg:hidden" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
      </a>

      <!-- Desktop Nav -->
      <nav aria-label="Main navigation" class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-8">
        <a href="/platform" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Platform
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/solutions" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Solutions
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/how-it-works" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">How It Works</a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/resources" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Resources
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </nav>

      <!-- Desktop CTAs -->
      <div class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-4">
        <a href="https://app.safetrekr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sm font-semibold transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-foreground" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Sign In</a>
        <a href="/demo" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center font-semibold rounded-md transition-all duration-150 text-white" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); background: var(--color-primary-600); padding: 10px 20px; font-size: 15px; border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none;">Get a Demo</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Mobile Hamburger -->
      <button id="mobile-menu-btn" class="lg:hidden p-2 text-foreground" aria-label="Open navigation menu" aria-expanded="false">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h16"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       IN-PAGE NAVIGATION (Sticky, appears on scroll)
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <nav id="page-nav" class="page-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
    <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">
      <div class="page-nav-inner flex items-center lg:justify-center gap-0">
        <a href="#challenge" class="page-nav-link" data-section="challenge">The Challenge</a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="page-nav-link" data-section="how-it-works">How It Works</a>
        <a href="#sample-binder" class="page-nav-link" data-section="sample-binder">Sample Binder</a>
        <a href="#pricing" class="page-nav-link" data-section="pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="#compliance" class="page-nav-link" data-section="compliance">Security</a>
        <a href="#faq" class="page-nav-link" data-section="faq">FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       MAIN CONTENT
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────
         SECTION 1: HERO
         ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="hero" aria-label="Hero" style="background: var(--color-background);" class="pt-8 pb-12 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-16 md:pt-16 md:pb-20 lg:pt-20 lg:pb-28 xl:pt-28 xl:pb-36">
      <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">

        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 lg:mb-8">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
            <li><a href="/" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Home</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li><a href="/solutions" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Solutions</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li aria-current="page" class="font-medium" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Corporate &amp; Sports Teams</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
          <!-- Text Column -->
          <div>
            <!-- Eyebrow -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-5">
              <!-- Building icon -->
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="4" y="2" width="16" height="20" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M9 22v-4h6v4"/><path d="M8 6h.01"/><path d="M16 6h.01"/><path d="M12 6h.01"/><path d="M12 10h.01"/><path d="M12 14h.01"/><path d="M16 10h.01"/><path d="M16 14h.01"/><path d="M8 10h.01"/><path d="M8 14h.01"/></svg>
              <span class="text-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">BUSINESS &amp; SPORTS TRAVEL SAFETY</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Headline -->
            <h1 class="text-display-xl max-w-[20ch]" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
              Enterprise Safety at Per-Trip Pricing
            </h1>

            <!-- Subheadline -->
            <p class="text-body-lg max-w-[50ch] mt-6" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
              SafeTrekr brings the same professional safety review that Fortune 500 companies use for executive travel to every business trip, team retreat, and tournament your organization sends. Government intelligence. 17-section analyst review. Duty of care documentation that protects your people and your organization.
            </p>

            <!-- CTAs -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
              <a href="/resources/sample-binders/corporate-travel" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary" aria-label="Download Corporate Travel Sample Binder, opens email-gated form">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                Download Corporate Travel Sample Binder
              </a>
              <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-lg btn-secondary" aria-label="Get a Demo -- opens scheduling page">
                Get a Demo
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual Column -->
          <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end">
            <div class="hero-visual" aria-hidden="true">
              <p class="sr-only">Composed interface showing a corporate travel safety binder with map intelligence, analyst review status, and evidence documentation.</p>

              <!-- Map Fragment (Southeast Asia region) -->
              <div class="hero-map">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 480 360" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <!-- Desaturated map background -->
                  <rect width="480" height="360" fill="#d4dce0"/>
                  <!-- Land masses (simplified SE Asia) -->
                  <path d="M60 80 Q120 60 180 90 L200 140 Q190 180 170 200 L140 210 Q100 190 80 160 Z" fill="#c8d3d8" stroke="#b8c3c7" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  <path d="M200 50 Q260 30 320 60 L340 120 Q330 160 300 180 L260 190 Q230 170 210 140 Z" fill="#c8d3d8" stroke="#b8c3c7" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  <path d="M340 100 Q380 80 420 110 L440 170 Q430 220 400 240 L360 250 Q330 230 320 200 Z" fill="#c8d3d8" stroke="#b8c3c7" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  <path d="M250 200 Q290 190 330 210 L350 260 Q340 300 310 320 L270 330 Q240 310 230 280 Z" fill="#c8d3d8" stroke="#b8c3c7" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                  <!-- Route path -->
